Yes, it happens in games like The Lion King, Dr Mario, Agro Soar, and some others.<br /><br />The game calculates the color as 11, which with pallette = 0x1B  means the color is BLACK, and as I understand, white is the transparent color for sprites.<br /><br />The weird thing is that BGB also shows those tiles with a black background, so I think my algorythm is correct.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=7082">DarkMoe</a> — Mon Jun 29, 2015 1:02 pm</p><hr />
